---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Arhum Savera — Senior Software Engineer building production AI systems, backend platforms, and developer tooling.">
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>
      Senior Software Engineer with 7+ years across backend platforms,
      applied ML, and production AI systems.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="about-profile">
      <div class="about-photo-wrap">
        <img
          src="/images/arhumsavera-profile.png"
          alt="Portrait of Arhum Savera"
          class="about-photo"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="panel about-intro">
        <h2>The gap between a working demo and a working system is where I live.</h2>
        <p>
          I started as a software engineer in Karachi, did an MS at UMass, then
          joined Signify for what I expected to be ML research — and learned that
          building computer vision for light bulb matching is genuinely hard. Users
          photograph their old bulb in bad kitchen lighting from four feet away and
          expect a correct SKU. That constraint forced me to care about real-world
          input variance, not benchmark accuracy.
        </p>
        <p>
          Amazon was next. I owned the CV pipeline for Dash Cart — real-time item
          recognition on Nvidia edge devices in 100+ live grocery stores. The system
          has to stay confident enough to charge you for things without constant cloud
          connectivity. A lot of the work was making failure modes bounded: a bad
          inference batch should trigger an alert, not silently degrade.
        </p>
        <p>
          Four years at ConsumerAffairs after that. The Kafka backbone didn't exist
          when I arrived. Neither did the AI content platform. The lead processing
          system existed but was held together with scheduling hacks and direct DB
          queries that would occasionally cascade. I spent four years owning these
          systems end to end — building them, running them, fixing them at odd hours.
        </p>
        <p>
          In early 2026 I went independent. I wanted to work on agent infrastructure
          before it became someone else's solved problem — specifically the parts
          nobody had built well: persistent memory across sessions, orchestration
          for long-running LLM workflows, and a local voice interface that doesn't
          route your code through a cloud API. Three tools I needed and couldn't find.
        </p>
        <p class="setup-line">
          Currently on Ghostty + tmux + Zed, coding remotely from an iPad over Tailscale more often than I should admit.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Currently Listening</h2>
    <iframe
      style="border-radius:12px"
      src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/playlist/5AQ1O6FZAzv9ujUObmTCTd?utm_source=generator"
      width="100%"
      height="152"
      frameborder="0"
      allowfullscreen
      allow="autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture"
      loading="lazy"
    ></iframe>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Selected Work</h2>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <a class="card" href="/post/consumeraffairs-ai-platform/">
        <h3>ConsumerAffairs: AI Platform</h3>
        <p>Built the AI content platform and Kafka backbone at ConsumerAffairs from scratch. Review moderation cut manual workload 80%; event streaming improved analytics throughput 5x.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="card" href="/post/digibrain/">
        <h3>Digibrain</h3>
        <p>Persistent shared memory for AI agents across sessions. Tree-index retrieval, structured SQLite store, Telegram bridge, and scheduled consolidation flows.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="card" href="/post/speakeasy/">
        <h3>SpeakEasy</h3>
        <p>100% local voice interface for CLI agents — Whisper for dictation, Kokoro for TTS, warm servers so there's no cold-start. No cloud APIs, works offline.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="card" href="/post/amazon-dash-cart/">
        <h3>Amazon Dash Cart</h3>
        <p>Real-time item recognition on Nvidia edge devices in 100+ live grocery stores. Inference optimization, GPU video encoding, and a six-week KMS encryption rollout across four teams.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Career</h2>
    <div class="panel timeline">
      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-meta">
          <span class="tl-date">2021 &ndash; Present</span>
          <span class="tl-company">ConsumerAffairs</span>
        </div>
        <div class="tl-body">
          <strong>Senior Software Engineer</strong> &middot; Remote
          <p>Built a greenfield AI content platform (FastAPI, LangChain, OpenAI, pgvector) for review moderation and summarization — 10x faster filtering, ~80% reduction in manual review. Designed the Kafka event streaming backbone across 8+ microservices (5x throughput). Built async budget enforcement and CPL pricing systems, cutting DB load by 40% and Redis calls by 60%. ML-driven lead scoring pipeline via Databricks over Kafka.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-meta">
          <span class="tl-date">2020 &ndash; 2021</span>
          <span class="tl-company">Amazon</span>
        </div>
        <div class="tl-body">
          <strong>Research Engineer</strong> &middot; Boston, MA
          <p>Owned the CV pipeline for Amazon Dash Cart — TensorRT inference on Nvidia edge devices across 100+ production carts. Built GPU-accelerated video encoding with 40x size reduction. Delivered client-side KMS encryption across 4 teams in 6 weeks, zero regressions. Built MQTT messaging, DynamoDB/Lambda jobs, and CloudWatch observability fleet-wide.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-meta">
          <span class="tl-date">2018 &ndash; 2020</span>
          <span class="tl-company">Signify</span>
        </div>
        <div class="tl-body">
          <strong>ML Scientist / ML Intern</strong> &middot; Cambridge, MA
          <p>Built end-to-end ML pipeline for LightFinder using VGG, Mask-RCNN, and Siamese networks for image retrieval. Post-training quantization and iterative pruning achieved 60% model compression and 30% inference speedup. Deployed containerized inference services on AWS. Also designed multi-task satellite segmentation models.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-meta">
          <span class="tl-date">2016 &ndash; 2017</span>
          <span class="tl-company">Techlogix</span>
        </div>
        <div class="tl-body">
          <strong>Software Engineer</strong> &middot; Karachi, PK
          <p>SOAP services and middleware integrations in Java with IBM Integration Bus and WebSphere MQ for a major UAE money exchange. Built a web-based remittance system replacing manual correspondent bank processing.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Education</h2>
    <div class="panel timeline">
      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-meta">
          <span class="tl-date">2017 &ndash; 2019</span>
          <span class="tl-company">UMass Amherst</span>
        </div>
        <div class="tl-body">
          <strong>M.S. Computer Science</strong> &middot; Amherst, MA &middot; GPA 3.9
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-meta">
          <span class="tl-date">2012 &ndash; 2016</span>
          <span class="tl-company">NUCES</span>
        </div>
        <div class="tl-body">
          <strong>B.S. Computer Science</strong> &middot; Karachi, PK &middot; GPA 3.8
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style is:inline>
  .about-profile {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    grid-template-columns: 240px minmax(0, 1fr);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-photo-wrap {
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 18px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: linear-gradient(165deg, #171f2be0, #0f141cf2);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    position: sticky;
    top: 5rem;
  }

  .about-photo {
    width: 100%;
    height: 380px;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center center;
    display: block;
  }

  .setup-line {
    margin-top: 0.9rem !important;
    font-size: 0.82rem !important;
    color: #6a849e !important;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .about-intro h2 {
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2vw, 1.6rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  /* ── timeline ── */
  .timeline {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .tl-item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 180px minmax(0, 1fr);
    gap: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    padding: 1.1rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .tl-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .tl-meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.2rem;
    padding-top: 0.05rem;
  }

  .tl-date {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }

  .tl-company {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #7fbfff;
  }

  .tl-body strong {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .tl-body p {
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  @media (max-width: 940px) {
    .about-profile { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .about-photo { min-height: 260px; }
    .tl-item { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.25rem; }
  }
</style>
